<!--
    Test Case: visit_occurrence and visit_detail FK Reconciliation
    
    This test verifies that clinical domain events 
    get correctly assigned to both:
    1. visit_occurrence_id (top-level visit, Layer 1)
    2. visit_detail_id (most specific nested visit, if applicable)
    
    Scenario:
    - Parent Visit (IPD): Jan 1-30, 2024 → visit_occurrence only
    - Nested Visit 1 (IPD): Jan 5-15, 2024 → visit_detail (Layer 2)
    - Nested Visit 2 (PROC): Jan 8 10:00-12:00 → visit_detail (Layer 3)
    
    Events:
    1. Measurement on Jan 3 → vo_id=100, vd_id=NULL (in parent only)
    2. Measurement on Jan 8 11:00 → vo_id=100, vd_id=300 (in PROC, most specific)
    3. Measurement on Jan 10 → vo_id=100, vd_id=200 (in Nested Visit 1)
    4. Measurement on Jan 25 → vo_id=100, vd_id=NULL (in parent only)
    5. Condition Jan 25-27 → vo_id=100, vd_id=NULL (in parent only)
    6. Procedure on Feb 5 → vo_id=NULL, vd_id=NULL (no matching visit)
-->
